\begin_layout Theorem
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 be a convex body in 
\begin_inset Formula $\R^{n}$
\end_inset

 containing a cube of side length 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 around its centroid and contained in a cube of side length 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

.
 Algorithm 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathtt{CuttingPlaneVolume}$
\end_inset

 correctly computes the volume of 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 using 
\begin_inset Formula $O(n\log\frac{nR}{r})$
\end_inset

 centroid computations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
By Lemma 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "thm:Grunbaum"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 at each iteration,
 the volume of the remaining set 
\begin_inset Formula $K^{(k)}$
\end_inset

 decreases by a factor of at most 
\begin_inset Formula $(1-\frac{1}{e})$
\end_inset

.
 When the directional width along any axis is less than 
\begin_inset Formula $r/2$
\end_inset

 (namely 
\begin_inset Formula $\max_{x\in K}\left|e_{i}^{\top}x\right|\leq\frac{r}{2}$
\end_inset

),
 the algorithm stops cutting along that axis.
 So,
 just before the last cut along any axis,
 the width in that direction is at least 
\begin_inset Formula $r/2$
\end_inset

.
 Then,
 we use the center of gravity to cut.
 By Lemma 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "lem:width"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 the directional width along every axis of the surviving set is at least 
\begin_inset Formula $r/2(n+1)$
\end_inset

.
 Since the set always contains the origin,
 and the original set contains a cube of side length 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

,
 when the algorithm stops,
 it must be an axis-parallel cuboid with each side of length in the range 
\begin_inset Formula $[r/2(n+1),r/2]$
\end_inset

.
 So the final volume is at least 
\begin_inset Formula $(r/2(n+1))^{n}.$
\end_inset

 The initial volume is at most 
\begin_inset Formula $R^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore the number of iterations is at most 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\log_{(1-\frac{1}{e})}\left(\frac{R^{n}}{(r/2(n+1))^{n}}\right)=O\left(n\log(nR/r)\right).
\]

\end_inset

In each iteration,
 by Lemma 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "lem:centroid"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 the algorithm maintains the ratio of the volume of the original 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 to the current 
\begin_inset Formula $K^{(k)}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

